radiographic_examinations.findings: A dilated internal mammary artery flanked by paired dilated internal mammary veins communicating distally via a saccular fistula.
Closure of the fistula with only the left internal mammary artery visible; embolization coils can be seen in the distal section of the artery.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Fistula was occluded with coil embolization.
